        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[<h2><a class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" id="introducing-lighthouse-for-backstage"></a><a href="#introducing-lighthouse-for-backstage" aria-hidden="true" class="hash-link"><svg class="hash-link-icon" aria-hidden="true" height="16" version="1.1" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a>Introducing Lighthouse for Backstage</h2>
<p><img src="/blog/assets/3/lead.png" alt="image illustrating the Lighthouse plugin for Backstage"></p>
<p>We’re proud to announce that our first internal plugin at Spotify has been open-sourced as part of Backstage. This plugin works with the newly open-sourced <a href="https://github.com/spotify/lighthouse-audit-service">lighthouse-audit-service</a> to run and track Lighthouse audits for your websites.</p>
