        <title type="html"><![CDATA[What the heck is Backstage anyway?]]></title>
        <id>https://backstage.io/blog/2020/03/18/what-is-backstage.html</id>
        <link href="https://backstage.io/blog/2020/03/18/what-is-backstage.html"/>
        <updated>2020-03-18T06:00:00.000Z</updated>
        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[<p><img src="/blog/assets/2/spotify-labs-header.png" alt="img"></p>
<p>Two days ago, we released the open source version of <a href="https://backstage.io/">Backstage</a>, our homegrown developer portal. And we learned a thing or two via the feedback we received. So, I wanted to take this opportunity to further explain what we’re trying to do with Backstage — and more importantly, what we want to give to the greater engineering community beyond Spotify.</p>
]]></summary>
